44Ac 12:22 They shouted, "This is the voice of a god, not of a man."
44Ac 12:23 Immediately, because Herod did not give praise to God, an angel of the Lord struck him down, and he was eaten by worms and died.
44Ac 12:24 But the word of God continued to increase and spread.
44Ac 12:25 When Barnabas and Saul had finished their mission, they returned from Jerusalem, taking with them John, also called Mark.
44Ac 13:1 In the church at Antioch there were prophets and teachers£º Barnabas, Simeon called Niger, Lucius of Cyrene, Manaen (who had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch) and Saul.
