472Co 12:20 For I am afraid that when I come I may not find you as I want you to be, and you may not find me as you want me to be. I fear that there may be quarreling, jealousy, outbursts of anger, factions, slander, gossip, arrogance and disorder.
472Co 12:21 I am afraid that when I come again my God will humble me before you, and I will be grieved over many who have sinned earlier and have not repented of the impurity, sexual sin and debauchery in which they have indulged.
472Co 13:1 This will be my third visit to you. "Every matter must be established by the testimony of two or three witnesses."
472Co 13:2 I already gave you a warning when I was with you the second time. I now repeat it while absent£º On my return I will not spare those who sinned earlier or any of the others,
