48Gl 3:3 Are you so foolish? After beginning with the Spirit, are you now trying to attain your goal by human effort?
48Gl 3:4 Have you suffered so much for nothing--if it really was for nothing?
48Gl 3:5 Does God give you his Spirit and work miracles among you because you observe the law, or because you believe what you heard?
48Gl 3:6 Consider Abraham£º "He believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness."
48Gl 3:7 Understand, then, that those who believe are children of Abraham.
48Gl 3:8 The Scripture foresaw that God would justify the Gentiles by faith, and announced the gospel in advance to Abraham£º "All nations will be blessed through you."
48Gl 3:9 So those who have faith are blessed along with Abraham, the man of faith.
48Gl 3:10 All who rely on observing the law are under a curse, for it is written£º "Cursed is everyone who does not continue to do everything written in the Book of the Law."
48Gl 3:11 Clearly no one is justified before God by the law, because, "The righteous will live by faith."
