51Col 2:16 Therefore do not let anyone judge you by what you eat or drink, or with regard to a religious festival, a New Moon celebration or a Sabbath day.
51Col 2:17 These are a shadow of the things that were to come; the reality, however, is found in Christ.
51Col 2:18 Do not let anyone who delights in false humility and the worship of angels disqualify you for the prize. Such a person goes into great detail about what he has seen, and his unspiritual mind puffs him up with idle notions.
51Col 2:19 He has lost connection with the Head, from whom the whole body, supported and held together by its ligaments and sinews, grows as God causes it to grow.
51Col 2:20 Since you died with Christ to the basic principles of this world, why, as though you still belonged to it, do you submit to its rules£º
51Col 2:21 "Do not handle! Do not taste! Do not touch!"?
51Col 2:22 These are all destined to perish with use, because they are based on human commands and teachings.
51Col 2:23 Such regulations indeed have an appearance of wisdom, with their self-imposed worship, their false humility and their harsh treatment of the body, but they lack any value in restraining sensual indulgence.
51Col 3:1 Since, then, you have been raised with Christ, set your hearts on things above, where Christ is seated at the right hand of God.
51Col 3:2 Set your minds on things above, not on earthly things.
51Col 3:3 For you died, and your life is now hidden with Christ in God.
51Col 3:4 When Christ, who is your life, appears, then you also will appear with him in glory.
51Col 3:5 Put to death, therefore, whatever belongs to your earthly nature£º sexual immorality, impurity, lust, evil desires and greed, which is idolatry.
51Col 3:6 Because of these, the wrath of God is coming.
51Col 3:7 You used to walk in these ways, in the life you once lived.
51Col 3:8 But now you must rid yourselves of all such things as these£º anger, rage, malice, slander, and filthy language from your lips.
51Col 3:9 Do not lie to each other, since you have taken off your old self with its practices
51Col 3:10 and have put on the new self, which is being renewed in knowledge in the image of its Creator.
51Col 3:11 Here there is no Greek or Jew, circumcised or uncircumcised, barbarian, Scythian, slave or free, but Christ is all, and is in all.
51Col 3:12 Therefore, as God's chosen people, holy and dearly loved, clothe yourselves with compassion, kindness, humility, gentleness and patience.
51Col 3:13 Bear with each other and forgive whatever grievances you may have against one another. Forgive as the Lord forgave you.
51Col 3:14 And over all these virtues put on love, which binds them all together in perfect unity.
51Col 3:15 Let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts, since as members of one body you were called to peace. And be thankful.
51Col 3:16 Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly as you teach and admonish one another with all wisdom, and as you sing psalms, hymns and spiritual songs with gratitude in your hearts to God.
51Col 3:17 And whatever you do, whether in word or deed, do it all in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him.
51Col 3:18 Wives, submit to your husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.
51Col 3:19 Husbands, love your wives and do not be harsh with them.
51Col 3:20 Children, obey your parents in everything, for this pleases the Lord.
51Col 3:21 Fathers, do not embitter your children, or they will become discouraged.
51Col 3:22 Slaves, obey your earthly masters in everything; and do it, not only when their eye is on you and to win their favor, but with sincerity of heart and reverence for the Lord.
51Col 3:23 Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as working for the Lord, not for men,
51Col 3:24 since you know that you will receive an inheritance from the Lord as a reward. It is the Lord Christ you are serving.
51Col 3:25 Anyone who does wrong will be repaid for his wrong, and there is no favoritism.
51Col 4:1 Masters, provide your slaves with what is right and fair, because you know that you also have a Master in heaven.
51Col 4:2 Devote yourselves to prayer, being watchful and thankful.
51Col 4:3 And pray for us, too, that God may open a door for our message, so that we may proclaim the mystery of Christ, for which I am in chains.
51Col 4:4 Pray that I may proclaim it clearly, as I should.
51Col 4:5 Be wise in the way you act toward outsiders; make the most of every opportunity.
51Col 4:6 Let your conversation be always full of grace, seasoned with salt, so that you may know how to answer everyone.
51Col 4:7 Tychicus will tell you all the news about me. He is a dear brother, a faithful minister and fellow servant in the Lord.
51Col 4:8 I am sending him to you for the express purpose that you may know about our circumstances and that he may encourage your hearts.
51Col 4:9 He is coming with Onesimus, our faithful and dear brother, who is one of you. They will tell you everything that is happening here.
51Col 4:10 My fellow prisoner Aristarchus sends you his greetings, as does Mark, the cousin of Barnabas. (You have received instructions about him; if he comes to you, welcome him.)
51Col 4:11 Jesus, who is called Justus, also sends greetings. These are the only Jews among my fellow workers for the kingdom of God, and they have proved a comfort to me.
51Col 4:12 Epaphras, who is one of you and a servant of Christ Jesus, sends greetings. He is always wrestling in prayer for you, that you may stand firm in all the will of God, mature and fully assured.
51Col 4:13 I vouch for him that he is working hard for you and for those at Laodicea and Hierapolis.
51Col 4:14 Our dear friend Luke, the doctor, and Demas send greetings.
51Col 4:15 Give my greetings to the brothers at Laodicea, and to Nympha and the church in her house.
51Col 4:16 After this letter has been read to you, see that it is also read in the church of the Laodiceans and that you in turn read the letter from Laodicea.
51Col 4:17 Tell Archippus£º "See to it that you complete the work you have received in the Lord."
51Col 4:18 I, Paul, write this greeting in my own hand. Remember my chains. Grace be with you.
