541Tm 1:1 Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the command of God our Savior and of Christ Jesus our hope,
541Tm 1:2 To Timothy my true son in the faith£º Grace, mercy and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
541Tm 1:3 As I urged you when I went into Macedonia, stay there in Ephesus so that you may command certain men not to teach false doctrines any longer
541Tm 1:4 nor to devote themselves to myths and endless genealogies. These promote controversies rather than God's work--which is by faith.
541Tm 1:5 The goal of this command is love, which comes from a pure heart and a good conscience and a sincere faith.
541Tm 1:6 Some have wandered away from these and turned to meaningless talk.
541Tm 1:7 They want to be teachers of the law, but they do not know what they are talking about or what they so confidently affirm.
541Tm 1:8 We know that the law is good if one uses it properly.
541Tm 1:9 We also know that law is made not for the righteous but for lawbreakers and rebels, the ungodly and sinful, the unholy and irreligious; for those who kill their fathers or mothers, for murderers,
541Tm 1:10 for adulterers and perverts, for slave traders and liars and perjurers--and for whatever else is contrary to the sound doctrine
541Tm 1:11 that conforms to the glorious gospel of the blessed God, which he entrusted to me.
541Tm 1:12 I thank Christ Jesus our Lord, who has given me strength, that he considered me faithful, appointing me to his service.
541Tm 1:13 Even though I was once a blasphemer and a persecutor and a violent man, I was shown mercy because I acted in ignorance and unbelief.
541Tm 1:14 The grace of our Lord was poured out on me abundantly, along with the faith and love that are in Christ Jesus.
541Tm 1:15 Here is a trustworthy saying that deserves full acceptance£º Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners--of whom I am the worst.
541Tm 1:16 But for that very reason I was shown mercy so that in me, the worst of sinners, Christ Jesus might display his unlimited patience as an example for those who would believe on him and receive eternal life.
541Tm 1:17 Now to the King eternal, immortal, invisible, the only God, be honor and glory for ever and ever. Amen.
541Tm 1:18 Timothy, my son, I give you this instruction in keeping with the prophecies once made about you, so that by following them you may fight the good fight,
541Tm 1:19 holding on to faith and a good conscience. Some have rejected these and so have shipwrecked their faith.
541Tm 1:20 Among them are Hymenaeus and Alexander, whom I have handed over to Satan to be taught not to blaspheme.
541Tm 2:1 I urge, then, first of all, that requests, prayers, intercession and thanksgiving be made for everyone--
541Tm 2:2 for kings and all those in authority, that we may live peaceful and quiet lives in all godliness and holiness.
541Tm 2:3 This is good, and pleases God our Savior,
541Tm 2:4 who wants all men to be saved and to come to a knowledge of the truth.
541Tm 2:5 For there is one God and one mediator between God and men, the man Christ Jesus,
541Tm 2:6 who gave himself as a ransom for all men--the testimony given in its proper time.
541Tm 2:7 And for this purpose I was appointed a herald and an apostle--I am telling the truth, I am not lying--and a teacher of the true faith to the Gentiles.
541Tm 2:8 I want men everywhere to lift up holy hands in prayer, without anger or disputing.
541Tm 2:9 I also want women to dress modestly, with decency and propriety, not with braided hair or gold or pearls or expensive clothes,
541Tm 2:10 but with good deeds, appropriate for women who profess to worship God.
541Tm 2:11 A woman should learn in quietness and full submission.
541Tm 2:12 I do not permit a woman to teach or to have authority over a man; she must be silent.
541Tm 2:13 For Adam was formed first, then Eve.
541Tm 2:14 And Adam was not the one deceived; it was the woman who was deceived and became a sinner.
541Tm 2:15 But women will be saved through childbearing--if they continue in faith, love and holiness with propriety.
541Tm 3:1 Here is a trustworthy saying£º If anyone sets his heart on being an overseer, he desires a noble task.
541Tm 3:2 Now the overseer must be above reproach, the husband of but one wife, temperate, self-controlled, respectable, hospitable, able to teach,
541Tm 3:3 not given to drunkenness, not violent but gentle, not quarrelsome, not a lover of money.
541Tm 3:4 He must manage his own family well and see that his children obey him with proper respect.
541Tm 3:5 (If anyone does not know how to manage his own family, how can he take care of God's church?)
541Tm 3:6 He must not be a recent convert, or he may become conceited and fall under the same judgment as the devil.
541Tm 3:7 He must also have a good reputation with outsiders, so that he will not fall into disgrace and into the devil's trap.
541Tm 3:8 Deacons, likewise, are to be men worthy of respect, sincere, not indulging in much wine, and not pursuing dishonest gain.
541Tm 3:9 They must keep hold of the deep truths of the faith with a clear conscience.
541Tm 3:10 They must first be tested; and then if there is nothing against them, let them serve as deacons.
541Tm 3:11 In the same way, their wives are to be women worthy of respect, not malicious talkers but temperate and trustworthy in everything.
541Tm 3:12 A deacon must be the husband of but one wife and must manage his children and his household well.
541Tm 3:13 Those who have served well gain an excellent standing and great assurance in their faith in Christ Jesus.
541Tm 3:14 Although I hope to come to you soon, I am writing you these instructions so that,
541Tm 3:15 if I am delayed, you will know how people ought to conduct themselves in God's household, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and foundation of the truth.
541Tm 3:16 Beyond all question, the mystery of godliness is great£º He appeared in a body, was vindicated by the Spirit, was seen by angels, was preached among the nations, was believed on in the world, was taken up in glory.
541Tm 4:1 The Spirit clearly says that in later times some will abandon the faith and follow deceiving spirits and things taught by demons.
541Tm 4:2 Such teachings come through hypocritical liars, whose consciences have been seared as with a hot iron.
541Tm 4:3 They forbid people to marry and order them to abstain from certain foods, which God created to be received with thanksgiving by those who believe and who know the truth.
541Tm 4:4 For everything God created is good, and nothing is to be rejected if it is received with thanksgiving,
541Tm 4:5 because it is consecrated by the word of God and prayer.
541Tm 4:6 If you point these things out to the brothers, you will be a good minister of Christ Jesus, brought up in the truths of the faith and of the good teaching that you have followed.
541Tm 4:7 Have nothing to do with godless myths and old wives' tales; rather, train yourself to be godly.
541Tm 4:8 For physical training is of some value, but godliness has value for all things, holding promise for both the present life and the life to come.
541Tm 4:9 This is a trustworthy saying that deserves full acceptance
541Tm 4:10 (and for this we labor and strive), that we have put our hope in the living God, who is the Savior of all men, and especially of those who believe.
541Tm 4:11 Command and teach these things.
541Tm 4:12 Don't let anyone look down on you because you are young, but set an example for the believers in speech, in life, in love, in faith and in purity.
541Tm 4:13 Until I come, devote yourself to the public reading of Scripture, to preaching and to teaching.
541Tm 4:14 Do not neglect your gift, which was given you through a prophetic message when the body of elders laid their hands on you.
541Tm 4:15 Be diligent in these matters; give yourself wholly to them, so that everyone may see your progress.
541Tm 4:16 Watch your life and doctrine closely. Persevere in them, because if you do, you will save both yourself and your hearers.
541Tm 5:1 Do not rebuke an older man harshly, but exhort him as if he were your father. Treat younger men as brothers,
541Tm 5:2 older women as mothers, and younger women as sisters, with absolute purity.
541Tm 5:3 Give proper recognition to those widows who are really in need.
541Tm 5:4 But if a widow has children or grandchildren, these should learn first of all to put their religion into practice by caring for their own family and so repaying their parents and grandparents, for this is pleasing to God.
541Tm 5:5 The widow who is really in need and left all alone puts her hope in God and continues night and day to pray and to ask God for help.
541Tm 5:6 But the widow who lives for pleasure is dead even while she lives.
541Tm 5:7 Give the people these instructions, too, so that no one may be open to blame.
