601Pt 3:9 Do not repay evil with evil or insult with insult, but with blessing, because to this you were called so that you may inherit a blessing.
601Pt 3:10 For, "Whoever would love life and see good days must keep his tongue from evil and his lips from deceitful speech.
601Pt 3:11 He must turn from evil and do good; he must seek peace and pursue it.
601Pt 3:12 For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous and his ears are attentive to their prayer, but the face of the Lord is against those who do evil."
