66Rv 11:11 But after the three and a half days a breath of life from God entered them, and they stood on their feet, and terror struck those who saw them.
66Rv 11:12 Then they heard a loud voice from heaven saying to them, "Come up here." And they went up to heaven in a cloud, while their enemies looked on.
66Rv 11:13 At that very hour there was a severe earthquake and a tenth of the city collapsed. Seven thousand people were killed in the earthquake, and the survivors were terrified and gave glory to the God of heaven.
66Rv 11:14 The second woe has passed; the third woe is coming soon.
66Rv 11:15 The seventh angel sounded his trumpet, and there were loud voices in heaven, which said£º "The kingdom of the world has become the kingdom of our Lord and of his Christ, and he will reign for ever and ever."
66Rv 11:16 And the twenty-four elders, who were seated on their thrones before God, fell on their faces and worshiped God,
66Rv 11:17 saying£º "We give thanks to you, Lord God Almighty, the One who is and who was, because you have taken your great power and have begun to reign.
66Rv 11:18 The nations were angry; and your wrath has come. The time has come for judging the dead, and for rewarding your servants the prophets and your saints and those who reverence your name, both small and great--and for destroying those who destroy the earth."
66Rv 11:19 Then God's temple in heaven was opened, and within his temple was seen the ark of his covenant. And there came flashes of lightning, rumblings, peals of thunder, an earthquake and a great hailstorm.
66Rv 12:1 A great and wondrous sign appeared in heaven£º a woman clothed with the sun, with the moon under her feet and a crown of twelve stars on her head.
66Rv 12:2 She was pregnant and cried out in pain as she was about to give birth.
66Rv 12:3 Then another sign appeared in heaven£º an enormous red dragon with seven heads and ten horns and seven crowns on his heads.
66Rv 12:4 His tail swept a third of the stars out of the sky and flung them to the earth. The dragon stood in front of the woman who was about to give birth, so that he might devour her child the moment it was born.
66Rv 12:5 She gave birth to a son, a male child, who will rule all the nations with an iron scepter. And her child was snatched up to God and to his throne.
66Rv 12:6 The woman fled into the desert to a place prepared for her by God, where she might be taken care of for 1,260 days.
66Rv 12:7 And there was war in heaven. Michael and his angels fought against the dragon, and the dragon and his angels fought back.
66Rv 12:8 But he was not strong enough, and they lost their place in heaven.
66Rv 12:9 The great dragon was hurled down--that ancient serpent called the devil, or Satan, who leads the whole world astray. He was hurled to the earth, and his angels with him.
66Rv 12:10 Then I heard a loud voice in heaven say£º "Now have come the salvation and the power and the kingdom of our God, and the authority of his Christ. For the accuser of our brothers, who accuses them before our God day and night, has been hurled down.
66Rv 12:11 They overcame him by the blood of the Lamb and by the word of their testimony; they did not love their lives so much as to shrink from death.
66Rv 12:12 Therefore rejoice, you heavens and you who dwell in them! But woe to the earth and the sea, because the devil has gone down to you! He is filled with fury, because he knows that his time is short."
66Rv 12:13 When the dragon saw that he had been hurled to the earth, he pursued the woman who had given birth to the male child.
66Rv 12:14 The woman was given the two wings of a great eagle, so that she might fly to the place prepared for her in the desert, where she would be taken care of for a time, times and half a time, out of the serpent's reach.
66Rv 12:15 Then from his mouth the serpent spewed water like a river, to overtake the woman and sweep her away with the torrent.
66Rv 12:16 But the earth helped the woman by opening its mouth and swallowing the river that the dragon had spewed out of his mouth.
66Rv 12:17 Then the dragon was enraged at the woman and went off to make war against the rest of her offspring--those who obey God's commandments and hold to the testimony of Jesus.
66Rv 13:1 And the dragon stood on the shore of the sea. And I saw a beast coming out of the sea. He had ten horns and seven heads, with ten crowns on his horns, and on each head a blasphemous name.
66Rv 13:2 The beast I saw resembled a leopard, but had feet like those of a bear and a mouth like that of a lion. The dragon gave the beast his power and his throne and great authority.
66Rv 13:3 One of the heads of the beast seemed to have had a fatal wound, but the fatal wound had been healed. The whole world was astonished and followed the beast.
66Rv 13:4 Men worshiped the dragon because he had given authority to the beast, and they also worshiped the beast and asked, "Who is like the beast? Who can make war against him?"
66Rv 13:5 The beast was given a mouth to utter proud words and blasphemies and to exercise his authority for forty-two months.
66Rv 13:6 He opened his mouth to blaspheme God, and to slander his name and his dwelling place and those who live in heaven.
66Rv 13:7 He was given power to make war against the saints and to conquer them. And he was given authority over every tribe, people, language and nation.
66Rv 13:8 All inhabitants of the earth will worship the beast--all whose names have not been written in the book of life belonging to the Lamb that was slain from the creation of the world.
66Rv 13:9 He who has an ear, let him hear.
66Rv 13:10 If anyone is to go into captivity, into captivity he will go. If anyone is to be killed with the sword, with the sword he will be killed. This calls for patient endurance and faithfulness on the part of the saints.
66Rv 13:11 Then I saw another beast, coming out of the earth. He had two horns like a lamb, but he spoke like a dragon.
66Rv 13:12 He exercised all the authority of the first beast on his behalf, and made the earth and its inhabitants worship the first beast, whose fatal wound had been healed.
66Rv 13:13 And he performed great and miraculous signs, even causing fire to come down from heaven to earth in full view of men.
66Rv 13:14 Because of the signs he was given power to do on behalf of the first beast, he deceived the inhabitants of the earth. He ordered them to set up an image in honor of the beast who was wounded by the sword and yet lived.
66Rv 13:15 He was given power to give breath to the image of the first beast, so that it could speak and cause all who refused to worship the image to be killed.
66Rv 13:16 He also forced everyone, small and great, rich and poor, free and slave, to receive a mark on his right hand or on his forehead,
66Rv 13:17 so that no one could buy or sell unless he had the mark, which is the name of the beast or the number of his name.
66Rv 13:18 This calls for wisdom. If anyone has insight, let him calculate the number of the beast, for it is man's number. His number is 666.
66Rv 14:1 Then I looked, and there before me was the Lamb, standing on Mount Zion, and with him 144,000 who had his name and his Father's name written on their foreheads.
66Rv 14:2 And I heard a sound from heaven like the roar of rushing waters and like a loud peal of thunder. The sound I heard was like that of harpists playing their harps.
66Rv 14:3 And they sang a new song before the throne and before the four living creatures and the elders. No one could learn the song except the 144,000 who had been redeemed from the earth.
66Rv 14:4 These are those who did not defile themselves with women, for they kept themselves pure. They follow the Lamb wherever he goes. They were purchased from among men and offered as firstfruits to God and the Lamb.
66Rv 14:5 No lie was found in their mouths; they are blameless.
66Rv 14:6 Then I saw another angel flying in midair, and he had the eternal gospel to proclaim to those who live on the earth--to every nation, tribe, language and people.
66Rv 14:7 He said in a loud voice, "Fear God and give him glory, because the hour of his judgment has come. Worship him who made the heavens, the earth, the sea and the springs of water."
66Rv 14:8 A second angel followed and said, "Fallen! Fallen is Babylon the Great, which made all the nations drink the maddening wine of her adulteries."
66Rv 14:9 A third angel followed them and said in a loud voice£º "If anyone worships the beast and his image and receives his mark on the forehead or on the hand,
66Rv 14:10 he, too, will drink of the wine of God's fury, which has been poured full strength into the cup of his wrath. He will be tormented with burning sulfur in the presence of the holy angels and of the Lamb.
66Rv 14:11 And the smoke of their torment rises for ever and ever. There is no rest day or night for those who worship the beast and his image, or for anyone who receives the mark of his name."
66Rv 14:12 This calls for patient endurance on the part of the saints who obey God's commandments and remain faithful to Jesus.
66Rv 14:13 Then I heard a voice from heaven say, "Write£º Blessed are the dead who die in the Lord from now on." "Yes," says the Spirit, "they will rest from their labor, for their deeds will follow them."
66Rv 14:14 I looked, and there before me was a white cloud, and seated on the cloud was one "like a son of man" with a crown of gold on his head and a sharp sickle in his hand.
66Rv 14:15 Then another angel came out of the temple and called in a loud voice to him who was sitting on the cloud, "Take your sickle and reap, because the time to reap has come, for the harvest of the earth is ripe."
66Rv 14:16 So he who was seated on the cloud swung his sickle over the earth, and the earth was harvested.
66Rv 14:17 Another angel came out of the temple in heaven, and he too had a sharp sickle.
66Rv 14:18 Still another angel, who had charge of the fire, came from the altar and called in a loud voice to him who had the sharp sickle, "Take your sharp sickle and gather the clusters of grapes from the earth's vine, because its grapes are ripe."
66Rv 14:19 The angel swung his sickle on the earth, gathered its grapes and threw them into the great winepress of God's wrath.
66Rv 14:20 They were trampled in the winepress outside the city, and blood flowed out of the press, rising as high as the horses' bridles for a distance of 1,600 stadia.
66Rv 15:1 I saw in heaven another great and marvelous sign£º seven angels with the seven last plagues--last, because with them God's wrath is completed.
66Rv 15:2 And I saw what looked like a sea of glass mixed with fire and, standing beside the sea, those who had been victorious over the beast and his image and over the number of his name. They held harps given them by God
66Rv 15:3 and sang the song of Moses the servant of God and the song of the Lamb£º "Great and marvelous are your deeds, Lord God Almighty. Just and true are your ways, King of the ages.
66Rv 15:4 Who will not fear you, O Lord, and bring glory to your name? For you alone are holy. All nations will come and worship before you, for your righteous acts have been revealed."
66Rv 15:5 After this I looked and in heaven the temple, that is, the tabernacle of the Testimony, was opened.
66Rv 15:6 Out of the temple came the seven angels with the seven plagues. They were dressed in clean, shining linen and wore golden sashes around their chests.
66Rv 15:7 Then one of the four living creatures gave to the seven angels seven golden bowls filled with the wrath of God, who lives for ever and ever.
66Rv 15:8 And the temple was filled with smoke from the glory of God and from his power, and no one could enter the temple until the seven plagues of the seven angels were completed.
66Rv 16:1 Then I heard a loud voice from the temple saying to the seven angels, "Go, pour out the seven bowls of God's wrath on the earth."
66Rv 16:2 The first angel went and poured out his bowl on the land, and ugly and painful sores broke out on the people who had the mark of the beast and worshiped his image.
66Rv 16:3 The second angel poured out his bowl on the sea, and it turned into blood like that of a dead man, and every living thing in the sea died.
66Rv 16:4 The third angel poured out his bowl on the rivers and springs of water, and they became blood.
66Rv 16:5 Then I heard the angel in charge of the waters say£º "You are just in these judgments, you who are and who were, the Holy One, because you have so judged;
66Rv 16:6 for they have shed the blood of your saints and prophets, and you have given them blood to drink as they deserve."
66Rv 16:7 And I heard the altar respond£º "Yes, Lord God Almighty, true and just are your judgments."
66Rv 16:8 The fourth angel poured out his bowl on the sun, and the sun was given power to scorch people with fire.
66Rv 16:9 They were seared by the intense heat and they cursed the name of God, who had control over these plagues, but they refused to repent and glorify him.
66Rv 16:10 The fifth angel poured out his bowl on the throne of the beast, and his kingdom was plunged into darkness. Men gnawed their tongues in agony
66Rv 16:11 and cursed the God of heaven because of their pains and their sores, but they refused to repent of what they had done.
66Rv 16:12 The sixth angel poured out his bowl on the great river Euphrates, and its water was dried up to prepare the way for the kings from the East.
66Rv 16:13 Then I saw three evil spirits that looked like frogs; they came out of the mouth of the dragon, out of the mouth of the beast and out of the mouth of the false prophet.
66Rv 16:14 They are spirits of demons performing miraculous signs, and they go out to the kings of the whole world, to gather them for the battle on the great day of God Almighty.
66Rv 16:15 "Behold, I come like a thief! Blessed is he who stays awake and keeps his clothes with him, so that he may not go naked and be shamefully exposed."
66Rv 16:16 Then they gathered the kings together to the place that in Hebrew is called Armageddon.
66Rv 16:17 The seventh angel poured out his bowl into the air, and out of the temple came a loud voice from the throne, saying, "It is done!"
66Rv 16:18 Then there came flashes of lightning, rumblings, peals of thunder and a severe earthquake. No earthquake like it has ever occurred since man has been on earth, so tremendous was the quake.
66Rv 16:19 The great city split into three parts, and the cities of the nations collapsed. God remembered Babylon the Great and gave her the cup filled with the wine of the fury of his wrath.
66Rv 16:20 Every island fled away and the mountains could not be found.
66Rv 16:21 From the sky huge hailstones of about a hundred pounds each fell upon men. And they cursed God on account of the plague of hail, because the plague was so terrible.
66Rv 17:1 One of the seven angels who had the seven bowls came and said to me, "Come, I will show you the punishment of the great prostitute, who sits on many waters.
66Rv 17:2 With her the kings of the earth committed adultery and the inhabitants of the earth were intoxicated with the wine of her adulteries."
66Rv 17:3 Then the angel carried me away in the Spirit into a desert. There I saw a woman sitting on a scarlet beast that was covered with blasphemous names and had seven heads and ten horns.
66Rv 17:4 The woman was dressed in purple and scarlet, and was glittering with gold, precious stones and pearls. She held a golden cup in her hand, filled with abominable things and the filth of her adulteries.
66Rv 17:5 This title was written on her forehead£º MYSTERY BABYLON THE GREAT THE MOTHER OF PROSTITUTES AND OF THE ABOMINATIONS OF THE EARTH.
66Rv 17:6 I saw that the woman was drunk with the blood of the saints, the blood of those who bore testimony to Jesus. When I saw her, I was greatly astonished.
66Rv 17:7 Then the angel said to me£º "Why are you astonished? I will explain to you the mystery of the woman and of the beast she rides, which has the seven heads and ten horns.
66Rv 17:8 The beast, which you saw, once was, now is not, and will come up out of the Abyss and go to his destruction. The inhabitants of the earth whose names have not been written in the book of life from the creation of the world will be astonished when they see the beast, because he once was, now is not, and yet will come.
66Rv 17:9 "This calls for a mind with wisdom. The seven heads are seven hills on which the woman sits.
66Rv 17:10 They are also seven kings. Five have fallen, one is, the other has not yet come; but when he does come, he must remain for a little while.
66Rv 17:11 The beast who once was, and now is not, is an eighth king. He belongs to the seven and is going to his destruction.
66Rv 17:12 "The ten horns you saw are ten kings who have not yet received a kingdom, but who for one hour will receive authority as kings along with the beast.
66Rv 17:13 They have one purpose and will give their power and authority to the beast.
66Rv 17:14 They will make war against the Lamb, but the Lamb will overcome them because he is Lord of lords and King of kings--and with him will be his called, chosen and faithful followers."
66Rv 17:15 Then the angel said to me, "The waters you saw, where the prostitute sits, are peoples, multitudes, nations and languages.
66Rv 17:16 The beast and the ten horns you saw will hate the prostitute. They will bring her to ruin and leave her naked; they will eat her flesh and burn her with fire.
66Rv 17:17 For God has put it into their hearts to accomplish his purpose by agreeing to give the beast their power to rule, until God's words are fulfilled.
66Rv 17:18 The woman you saw is the great city that rules over the kings of the earth."
66Rv 18:1 After this I saw another angel coming down from heaven. He had great authority, and the earth was illuminated by his splendor.
66Rv 18:2 With a mighty voice he shouted£º "Fallen! Fallen is Babylon the Great! She has become a home for demons and a haunt for every evil spirit, a haunt for every unclean and detestable bird.
66Rv 18:3 For all the nations have drunk the maddening wine of her adulteries. The kings of the earth committed adultery with her, and the merchants of the earth grew rich from her excessive luxuries."
66Rv 18:4 Then I heard another voice from heaven say£º "Come out of her, my people, so that you will not share in her sins, so that you will not receive any of her plagues;
66Rv 18:5 for her sins are piled up to heaven, and God has remembered her crimes.
66Rv 18:6 Give back to her as she has given; pay her back double for what she has done. Mix her a double portion from her own cup.
66Rv 18:7 Give her as much torture and grief as the glory and luxury she gave herself. In her heart she boasts, 'I sit as queen; I am not a widow, and I will never mourn.'
66Rv 18:8 Therefore in one day her plagues will overtake her£º death, mourning and famine. She will be consumed by fire, for mighty is the Lord God who judges her.
66Rv 18:9 "When the kings of the earth who committed adultery with her and shared her luxury see the smoke of her burning, they will weep and mourn over her.
66Rv 18:10 Terrified at her torment, they will stand far off and cry£º "'Woe! Woe, O great city, O Babylon, city of power! In one hour your doom has come!'
66Rv 18:11 "The merchants of the earth will weep and mourn over her because no one buys their cargoes any more--
66Rv 18:12 cargoes of gold, silver, precious stones and pearls; fine linen, purple, silk and scarlet cloth; every sort of citron wood, and articles of every kind made of ivory, costly wood, bronze, iron and marble;
66Rv 18:13 cargoes of cinnamon and spice, of incense, myrrh and frankincense, of wine and olive oil, of fine flour and wheat; cattle and sheep; horses and carriages; and bodies and souls of men.
66Rv 18:14 "They will say, 'The fruit you longed for is gone from you. All your riches and splendor have vanished, never to be recovered.'
66Rv 18:15 The merchants who sold these things and gained their wealth from her will stand far off, terrified at her torment. They will weep and mourn
66Rv 18:16 and cry out£º "'Woe! Woe, O great city, dressed in fine linen, purple and scarlet, and glittering with gold, precious stones and pearls!
66Rv 18:17 In one hour such great wealth has been brought to ruin!' "Every sea captain, and all who travel by ship, the sailors, and all who earn their living from the sea, will stand far off.
66Rv 18:18 When they see the smoke of her burning, they will exclaim, 'Was there ever a city like this great city?'
66Rv 18:19 They will throw dust on their heads, and with weeping and mourning cry out£º "'Woe! Woe, O great city, where all who had ships on the sea became rich through her wealth! In one hour she has been brought to ruin!
66Rv 18:20 Rejoice over her, O heaven! Rejoice, saints and apostles and prophets! God has judged her for the way she treated you.'"
66Rv 18:21 Then a mighty angel picked up a boulder the size of a large millstone and threw it into the sea, and said£º "With such violence the great city of Babylon will be thrown down, never to be found again.
66Rv 18:22 The music of harpists and musicians, flute players and trumpeters, will never be heard in you again. No workman of any trade will ever be found in you again. The sound of a millstone will never be heard in you again.
66Rv 18:23 The light of a lamp will never shine in you again. The voice of bridegroom and bride will never be heard in you again. Your merchants were the world's great men. By your magic spell all the nations were led astray.
66Rv 18:24 In her was found the blood of prophets and of the saints, and of all who have been killed on the earth."
66Rv 19:1 After this I heard what sounded like the roar of a great multitude in heaven shouting£º "Hallelujah! Salvation and glory and power belong to our God,
66Rv 19:2 for true and just are his judgments. He has condemned the great prostitute who corrupted the earth by her adulteries. He has avenged on her the blood of his servants."
66Rv 19:3 And again they shouted£º "Hallelujah! The smoke from her goes up for ever and ever."
66Rv 19:4 The twenty-four elders and the four living creatures fell down and worshiped God, who was seated on the throne. And they cried£º "Amen, Hallelujah!"
66Rv 19:5 Then a voice came from the throne, saying£º "Praise our God, all you his servants, you who fear him, both small and great!"
66Rv 19:6 Then I heard what sounded like a great multitude, like the roar of rushing waters and like loud peals of thunder, shouting£º "Hallelujah! For our Lord God Almighty reigns.
66Rv 19:7 Let us rejoice and be glad and give him glory! For the wedding of the Lamb has come, and his bride has made herself ready.
66Rv 19:8 Fine linen, bright and clean, was given her to wear." (Fine linen stands for the righteous acts of the saints.)
66Rv 19:9 Then the angel said to me, "Write£º 'Blessed are those who are invited to the wedding supper of the Lamb!'" And he added, "These are the true words of God."
66Rv 19:10 At this I fell at his feet to worship him. But he said to me, "Do not do it! I am a fellow servant with you and with your brothers who hold to the testimony of Jesus. Worship God! For the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy."
66Rv 19:11 I saw heaven standing open and there before me was a white horse, whose rider is called Faithful and True. With justice he judges and makes war.
66Rv 19:12 His eyes are like blazing fire, and on his head are many crowns. He has a name written on him that no one knows but he himself.
66Rv 19:13 He is dressed in a robe dipped in blood, and his name is the Word of God.
66Rv 19:14 The armies of heaven were following him, riding on white horses and dressed in fine linen, white and clean.
66Rv 19:15 Out of his mouth comes a sharp sword with which to strike down the nations. "He will rule them with an iron scepter." He treads the winepress of the fury of the wrath of God Almighty.
66Rv 19:16 On his robe and on his thigh he has this name written£º KING OF KINGS AND LORD OF LORDS.
66Rv 19:17 And I saw an angel standing in the sun, who cried in a loud voice to all the birds flying in midair, "Come, gather together for the great supper of God,
66Rv 19:18 so that you may eat the flesh of kings, generals, and mighty men, of horses and their riders, and the flesh of all people, free and slave, small and great."
66Rv 19:19 Then I saw the beast and the kings of the earth and their armies gathered together to make war against the rider on the horse and his army.
66Rv 19:20 But the beast was captured, and with him the false prophet who had performed the miraculous signs on his behalf. With these signs he had deluded those who had received the mark of the beast and worshiped his image. The two of them were thrown alive into the fiery lake of burning sulfur.
66Rv 19:21 The rest of them were killed with the sword that came out of the mouth of the rider on the horse, and all the birds gorged themselves on their flesh.
66Rv 20:1 And I saw an angel coming down out of heaven, having the key to the Abyss and holding in his hand a great chain.
66Rv 20:2 He seized the dragon, that ancient serpent, who is the devil, or Satan, and bound him for a thousand years.
66Rv 20:3 He threw him into the Abyss, and locked and sealed it over him, to keep him from deceiving the nations anymore until the thousand years were ended. After that, he must be set free for a short time.
66Rv 20:4 I saw thrones on which were seated those who had been given authority to judge. And I saw the souls of those who had been beheaded because of their testimony for Jesus and because of the word of God. They had not worshiped the beast or his image and had not received his mark on their foreheads or their hands. They came to life and reigned with Christ a thousand years.
66Rv 20:5 (The rest of the dead did not come to life until the thousand years were ended.) This is the first resurrection.
66Rv 20:6 Blessed and holy are those who have part in the first resurrection. The second death has no power over them, but they will be priests of God and of Christ and will reign with him for a thousand years.
66Rv 20:7 When the thousand years are over, Satan will be released from his prison
66Rv 20:8 and will go out to deceive the nations in the four corners of the earth--Gog and Magog--to gather them for battle. In number they are like the sand on the seashore.
66Rv 20:9 They marched across the breadth of the earth and surrounded the camp of God's people, the city he loves. But fire came down from heaven and devoured them.
66Rv 20:10 And the devil, who deceived them, was thrown into the lake of burning sulfur, where the beast and the false prophet had been thrown. They will be tormented day and night for ever and ever.
66Rv 20:11 Then I saw a great white throne and him who was seated on it. Earth and sky fled from his presence, and there was no place for them.
66Rv 20:12 And I saw the dead, great and small, standing before the throne, and books were opened. Another book was opened, which is the book of life. The dead were judged according to what they had done as recorded in the books.
66Rv 20:13 The sea gave up the dead that were in it, and death and Hades gave up the dead that were in them, and each person was judged according to what he had done.
66Rv 20:14 Then death and Hades were thrown into the lake of fire. The lake of fire is the second death.
66Rv 20:15 If anyone's name was not found written in the book of life, he was thrown into the lake of fire.
66Rv 21:1 Then I saw a new heaven and a new earth, for the first heaven and the first earth had passed away, and there was no longer any sea.
66Rv 21:2 I saw the Holy City, the new Jerusalem, coming down out of heaven from God, prepared as a bride beautifully dressed for her husband.
66Rv 21:3 And I heard a loud voice from the throne saying, "Now the dwelling of God is with men, and he will live with them. They will be his people, and God himself will be with them and be their God.
66Rv 21:4 He will wipe every tear from their eyes. There will be no more death or mourning or crying or pain, for the old order of things has passed away."
66Rv 21:5 He who was seated on the throne said, "I am making everything new!" Then he said, "Write this down, for these words are trustworthy and true."
66Rv 21:6 He said to me£º "It is done. I am the Alpha and the Omega, the Beginning and the End. To him who is thirsty I will give to drink without cost from the spring of the water of life.
66Rv 21:7 He who overcomes will inherit all this, and I will be his God and he will be my son.
66Rv 21:8 But the cowardly, the unbelieving, the vile, the murderers, the sexually immoral, those who practice magic arts, the idolaters and all liars--their place will be in the fiery lake of burning sulfur. This is the second death."
66Rv 21:9 One of the seven angels who had the seven bowls full of the seven last plagues came and said to me, "Come, I will show you the bride, the wife of the Lamb."
66Rv 21:10 And he carried me away in the Spirit to a mountain great and high, and showed me the Holy City, Jerusalem, coming down out of heaven from God.
66Rv 21:11 It shone with the glory of God, and its brilliance was like that of a very precious jewel, like a jasper, clear as crystal.
66Rv 21:12 It had a great, high wall with twelve gates, and with twelve angels at the gates. On the gates were written the names of the twelve tribes of Israel.
66Rv 21:13 There were three gates on the east, three on the north, three on the south and three on the west.
66Rv 21:14 The wall of the city had twelve foundations, and on them were the names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.
66Rv 21:15 The angel who talked with me had a measuring rod of gold to measure the city, its gates and its walls.
66Rv 21:16 The city was laid out like a square, as long as it was wide. He measured the city with the rod and found it to be 12,000 stadia in length, and as wide and high as it is long.
66Rv 21:17 He measured its wall and it was 144 cubits thick, by man's measurement, which the angel was using.
66Rv 21:18 The wall was made of jasper, and the city of pure gold, as pure as glass.
66Rv 21:19 The foundations of the city walls were decorated with every kind of precious stone. The first foundation was jasper, the second sapphire, the third chalcedony, the fourth emerald,
66Rv 21:20 the fifth sardonyx, the sixth carnelian, the seventh chrysolite, the eighth beryl, the ninth topaz, the tenth chrysoprase, the eleventh jacinth, and the twelfth amethyst.
66Rv 21:21 The twelve gates were twelve pearls, each gate made of a single pearl. The great street of the city was of pure gold, like transparent glass.
66Rv 21:22 I did not see a temple in the city, because the Lord God Almighty and the Lamb are its temple.
66Rv 21:23 The city does not need the sun or the moon to shine on it, for the glory of God gives it light, and the Lamb is its lamp.
66Rv 21:24 The nations will walk by its light, and the kings of the earth will bring their splendor into it.
66Rv 21:25 On no day will its gates ever be shut, for there will be no night there.
66Rv 21:26 The glory and honor of the nations will be brought into it.
66Rv 21:27 Nothing impure will ever enter it, nor will anyone who does what is shameful or deceitful, but only those whose names are written in the Lamb's book of life.
66Rv 22:1 Then the angel showed me the river of the water of life, as clear as crystal, flowing from the throne of God and of the Lamb
66Rv 22:2 down the middle of the great street of the city. On each side of the river stood the tree of life, bearing twelve crops of fruit, yielding its fruit every month. And the leaves of the tree are for the healing of the nations.
66Rv 22:3 No longer will there be any curse. The throne of God and of the Lamb will be in the city, and his servants will serve him.
66Rv 22:4 They will see his face, and his name will be on their foreheads.
66Rv 22:5 There will be no more night. They will not need the light of a lamp or the light of the sun, for the Lord God will give them light. And they will reign for ever and ever.
66Rv 22:6 The angel said to me, "These words are trustworthy and true. The Lord, the God of the spirits of the prophets, sent his angel to show his servants the things that must soon take place."
66Rv 22:7 "Behold, I am coming soon! Blessed is he who keeps the words of the prophecy in this book."
66Rv 22:8 I, John, am the one who heard and saw these things. And when I had heard and seen them, I fell down to worship at the feet of the angel who had been showing them to me.
66Rv 22:9 But he said to me, "Do not do it! I am a fellow servant with you and with your brothers the prophets and of all who keep the words of this book. Worship God!"
66Rv 22:10 Then he told me, "Do not seal up the words of the prophecy of this book, because the time is near.
66Rv 22:11 Let him who does wrong continue to do wrong; let him who is vile continue to be vile; let him who does right continue to do right; and let him who is holy continue to be holy."
66Rv 22:12 "Behold, I am coming soon! My reward is with me, and I will give to everyone according to what he has done.
66Rv 22:13 I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the Beginning and the End.
66Rv 22:14 "Blessed are those who wash their robes, that they may have the right to the tree of life and may go through the gates into the city.
66Rv 22:15 Outside are the dogs, those who practice magic arts, the sexually immoral, the murderers, the idolaters and everyone who loves and practices falsehood.
66Rv 22:16 "I, Jesus, have sent my angel to give you this testimony for the churches. I am the Root and the Offspring of David, and the bright Morning Star."
66Rv 22:17 The Spirit and the bride say, "Come!" And let him who hears say, "Come!" Whoever is thirsty, let him come; and whoever wishes, let him take the free gift of the water of life.
66Rv 22:18 I warn everyone who hears the words of the prophecy of this book£º If anyone adds anything to them, God will add to him the plagues described in this book.
66Rv 22:19 And if anyone takes words away from this book of prophecy, God will take away from him his share in the tree of life and in the holy city, which are described in this book.
66Rv 22:20 He who testifies to these things says, "Yes, I am coming soon." Amen. Come, Lord Jesus.
66Rv 22:21 The grace of the Lord Jesus be with God's people. Amen.
